        whyItMatters: 'Every investor pass, every deal that doesn\'t close, every feature that doesn\'t land — don\'t judge the decision by the outcome. Evaluate the process. Did you have the right information? Did you consider the alternatives? Did you identify the key risks? If yes: it was a good decision. Learn from the outcome, but don\'t let it reprice the quality of your reasoning.',
        action: 'Identify one past decision that had a bad outcome but was well-reasoned. Write a 1-paragraph defense of the decision quality, separate from the outcome. Practice presenting it.',
